Again, I am engaging with you on my personal Twitter as Carmen, not OVER.

For one side of the story, indeed, it would seem that way. On the other side of the story, it is not this way at all.

I have received DMs saying that the way Hex uses the word "community" does not represent the entire OVER community at all.

@hexidized @soyocrypto @MVMFPresents @OVRtheReality @diego_DDT_ I disagree. This is absolutely not true. Then again, this is your perception.

@hexidized @soyocrypto @MVMFPresents @OVRtheReality @diego_DDT_ So you do not feel that all these allegations you have posted on multiple social media accounts, blaming OVER for being involved with DCL and holding them responsible for DCL's MVMF brand is not attacking?

The team felt attacked and did not know where it was all coming from.
@Binx3ps Hey @Binx3ps! Yeah, true. FYI, @hexidized is like a brother to me .. a younger brother :)

Disclosure: I was given a copy to post on OVER socials with wording that would just not go well. I chose to edit the copy. Unfortunately, we were given an image by DCL to use for a blog post üò¶.

@fishbrainLtd @hexidized @OVRtheReality @MVMFPresents @decentraland Hi @fishbrainLtd. Do you mean DCL knew or OVER knew? It's nice to see you here. Although, unfortunately it could be under better circumstances :)

@soyocrypto @MVMFPresents @OVRtheReality @hexidized Tit for Tat. You got involved where you didn't need to.
I respect your support for @hexidized.

"it's all good to push around a smaller DAO project"???

I have not and will not push around anyone.
I merely said to you, ‚¨áÔ∏è.

You see that as "throwing punches"? https://t.co/i0WLDzCLSj

Companies are run by people. Back in 2010, I attended @jeffpulver's #BrandConf where the topic was humanizing brands online. 

When someone personally attacks a company with the wrong facts and continues to do so, it is the responsibility of the team to step up and step in.

@soyocrypto @MVMFPresents @OVRtheReality @hexidized @hexidized chose to air whatever he wanted to air. 
He has gone too far, so I decided to engage with him on Twitter. Hex has said things that are not true. If people ONLY read his POV, then it would not be fair to OVER.

I came on to set the story straight.
There are two sides.

Agree. This is why I made the decision to have a public conversation with you on Twitter, for all to see, @hexidized.

I did not like how you were lambasting @OVRtheReality, based on your perceptions and whatever expectations you set out. You have the right to your opinion, too.

@hexidized @OVRtheReality What am I doing that is wrong?

Can't I share my opinions on this matter, as you have chosen to do?

Are you also going to paint me as a person in the wrong, as you have with OVER?

What am I now doing wrong?

Yup. @OVRtheReality was in talks with @hexidized and they were starting to talk about the scope of work/deliverables. For some reason, Hex did not want OVER's offer. He has the right to negotiate, however, he is blowing up a situation and wants to control the narrative.

Perception is a reality‚¨áÔ∏è

"Your right they are showing how metaverse brands can steal from their communities and get away with it"
- @hexidized

You are wrong. @OVRtheReality's partnership with DCL is showing the world how seemingly competing companies can work together in Web3. https://t.co/tEbCOW4tIK

Dear OVER Community & @MVMFPresents. I handle @OVRtheReality's Twitter account.

A situation arose where @hexidized is fighting for the rights of a group of people. While I respect his intentions and perceptions, I feel that his accusations against OVER are incorrect. Just sayin'

@hexidized @OVRtheReality If monetary compensation is a perk then great. Just don't spread rumours that @OVRtheReality's partnership with DCL is about money. OVER is doing this to show how Metaverse brands can come together, and of course, to showcase their technology.

How much did you ask OVER to fork out when you sent them your proposal?? So don't speak to me about "money".

Don't say that with OVER it is about money. That is not how @OVRtheReality is. Absolutely not. 

They are not getting any money for this DCL event. #FACT

This is NOT about money, DUDE!!!! Do you know that there is no $$$ or tokens exchanged between OVER + DCL for this "Metaverse Music Festival"???

This is simply two Metaverses joining forces, with their resources, showing what can be done in Web3!!!!

@hexidized @OVRtheReality @MVMFPresents @decentraland Indeed, they do know now.
Indeed,  it was not until you went all emotional in public ... I believe they did not change their response. I was told they made an offer and you refused their offer.

No one stabbed you in the back, @hexidized. I get why you choose to use this strong, visual statement. For impact.

I'm sorry you feel this way. Again, perceptions and expectations need to be managed, here.

OVER did nothing wrong, in my opinion. https://t.co/plX7Gltz8k

@hexidized @OVRtheReality I understand how you feel. If I really believed that OVER is in the wrong, I would not hesitate to make my opinions known.

In this case, I see both sides & can honestly say that this is unfortunate timing & that OVER is not in the wrong. And I wouldn't want them to back out. üëÄ

@hexidized @OVRtheReality @MVMFPresents @decentraland Honestly, that is how I feel. These tweets are my own personal opinions at this given time.

OMG!!! Now you are turning it on ME???
You KNOW I support the community.
I am just here to talk it out.
This does not mean I do not support the commumity.

Wow!

The only stance that OVER (@OVRtheReality) is taking is showing the world that in #Web3, Metaverse brands can get together and provide amazing experiences for users.

If you can't see that then I don't know what to say other than: Perceptions & expectations need to be managed.

@hexidized @OVRtheReality @MVMFPresents @decentraland @facebook @Snapchat @Meta @instagram @Roblox @FortniteGame Why blame @OVRtheReality for a named event that @decentraland chose?

Yes, OVER partnered with DCL - to provide their platform to showcase how musicians/artists with a mocap suit can join in AR/VR during a real-life event.

@hexidized @TeamFireBadger2 @OVRtheReality @decentraland @MVMFPresents I tweet for @OVRtheReality. I am choosing to use my personal Twitter.

You are assuming that OVER had control over the timing of DCL's event & the naming of it. OVER's partnership only involves the provision of their platform & to showcase musicians w/ mocap suits in AR

@hexidized @OVRtheReality @MVMFPresents @decentraland So, OVER originally said that they would not be part of the MVMF because "They were already involved in something and could not take on more". That something was DCL and other projects.

I don't think OVER realized that DCL's "Metaverse Music Festival" and MVMF .... well.
Looks like it's time to head OVER to @OVRtheReality and send out a tweet :)

@hexidized @OVRtheReality @MVMFPresents I wasn't in any of these meetings/group chats btwn you + OVER. I only know they occurred. This is what I'm referring to as "collab" or "talks of one."

You said OVER declined b/c "they were already involved in something and could not take on more". Isn't that an honest response?

There are always two sides to every story.

Perceptions and expectations.
